<title>USA: Synopsys suspends stock repurchase.</title>
<headline>Synopsys suspends stock repurchase.</headline>
<dateline>MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif. 1997-02-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>Synopsys Inc said it suspended its stock repurchase program in order to comply with pooling-of-interests accounting rules in connection with its proposed merger with EPIC Design Technology Inc.</p>
<p>Last May, the company authorized a program to repurchase up to two million shares over a two-year period. It said that as of December 31, it had repurchased 566,389 shares.</p>
<p>On January 16, the company reached a definitive agreement to merge with EPIC. It said the repurchase program may be rescinded prior to the closing of the EPIC merger if necessary to comply with such pooling-of-interests guidance.</p>
